description:
'''Nação Zumbi''' (formerly '''Chico Science & Nação Zumbi''') is a Brazilian band formed by [[Chico Science]]. They have been hailed as one of the most important groups to come out of the [[Mangue Bit|manguebeat]] movement in the 1990s. The musicians of the group continued as Nação Zumbi after Science died in a car accident on February 2, 1997.{{fact|date=March 2025}}

In their songs they experiment with mixing of [[rock music|rock]], [[punk rock|punk]], [[funk]], [[hip hop music|hip hop]], [[soul music|soul]], [[Pernambuco]]'s regional rhythms and [[Music of Brazil|Brazilian traditional music]], with heavy use of [[percussion instrument]]s.{{fact|date=March 2025}}

They released two albums before the time of Chico's death, ''[[Da lama ao caos]]'' (''From Mud to Chaos'') in 1994 and ''Afrociberdelia'' in 1996. Both received critical acclaim.

In 1996, Nação Zumbi contributed ''Maracatu Atômico'' to the AIDS-Benefit Album [[Red Hot + Rio]] produced by the [[Red Hot Organization]].{{fact|date=March 2025}}
